    <title>Manage favorites</title>
    <para>Saving your charts or pivot tables as favorites makes it easy to find them later. You can
        also choose to share them with other users as an interpretation or display them on the
        dashboard.</para>
    <para>You view the details and interpretations of your favorites in the
            <?oxy_comment_start author="rachaelb" timestamp="20161010T224006+0200" comment="For 2.26 favorites will be also applied to: event reports, event visualizer, GIS" id="xfj_2mr_b1b" flag="done"?><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170531T145844+0200" comment="only GIS left on old model, will be changed in version 2.28

2.27: Event Visualizer and Event Reports got new favorite solution" parentID="xfj_2mr_b1b" flag="done" mid="1"?><emphasis
            role="bold">Pivot Table</emphasis>, <emphasis role="bold">Data Visualizer</emphasis>,
            <emphasis role="bold">Event Visualizer</emphasis>, <emphasis role="bold">Event
            Reports</emphasis> app<?oxy_comment_end mid="1"?><?oxy_comment_end?>s. Use the <emphasis
            role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> menu to manage your favorites.</para>
    <section>
        <title>Open a favorite</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                        >Open</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Enter the name of a favorite in the search field, or click <emphasis
                        role="bold">Prev</emphasis> and <emphasis role="bold">Next</emphasis> to
                    display favorites.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click the name of the favorite you want to open.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Save a favorite</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Save
                        as</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
<para>Enter a <emphasis role="bold">Name</emphasis> and a <emphasis role="bold"
                        >Description</emphasis> for your favorite.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Rename a favorite</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                        >Rename</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Enter the new name for your favorite.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Update</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Write an interpretation for a favorite</title>
        <para role="">An interpretation is a link to a resource with a description of the data at a
            given period. This information is visible in the <emphasis role="bold"
                >Dashboard</emphasis> app. To create an interpretation, you first need to create a
            favorite. If you've shared your favorite with other people, the interpretation you write
            is visible to those people.</para>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Write
                        interpretation</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
<para>In the text field, type a comment, question or interpretation. You can see this information in
                    the <emphasis role="bold">Dashboard</emphasis> app.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Search for a user group that you want to share your favorite with, then click
                    the <emphasis role="bold">+</emphasis> icon.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Change sharing settings for the user groups you want to modify.</para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">Can edit and view</emphasis>: Everyone can view
                            and edit the object.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">Can view only</emphasis>: Everyone can view the
                            object.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">None</emphasis>: The public won't have access to
                            the object. This setting is only applicable to <emphasis role="bold"
                                >Public access</emphasis>. </para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Share</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Create a link to a favorite</title>
        <para>
            <orderedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                            >Get link</emphasis>.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Select one of the following:</para>
                    <itemizedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para><emphasis role="bold">Open in this app</emphasis>: You get a URL
                                for the favorite which you can share with other users by email or
                                chat.</para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para><emphasis role="bold">Open in web api</emphasis>: You get a URL of
                                the API resource. By default this is an HTML resource, but you can
                                change the file extension to &quot;.json&quot; or
                                &quot;.csv&quot;.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
        </para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Delete a favorite</title>
        <para>
            <orderedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                            >Delete</emphasis>.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">OK</emphasis>.</para>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
        </para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>View interpretations based on relative periods</title>
        <para>To view interpretations for relative periods, such as a year ago:</para>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Open a favorite with interpretations.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">>>></emphasis> in the top right of the
                    workspace.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click an interpretation.
                    Y<?oxy_comment_start author="rachaelb" timestamp="20161011T155331+0200" comment="create screengrab"?>our
                    chart displays the data and the date based on when the interpretation was
                    created.<?oxy_comment_end?>To view other interpretations, click them.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
</section>
